data.name: LowNoiseSpurModeWarningIcon.ToolTip
data.value:
When using Low Spur Mode, MOD must be 50 or greater. To increase MOD, decrease the channel spacing. (PFD frequency / Channel spacing = MOD)
If you are using FRAC/MOD GCD mode, try disabling it. Untick Tools > Enable FRAC/MOD GCD.

data.name: PFDWarningIcon.ToolTip
data.value:
Frac-N mode: Maximum PFD frequency is 32 MHz.
Int-N mode (FRAC = 0): Maximum PFD frequency is 90 MHz. Band Select Clock Mode must be set High. PFD frequencies > 45 MHz require a special write sequence; see High PFD Frequencies section of the ADF4351 datasheet.

data.name: label74.Text
data.value:
Version 4.2 support the feature to export a configuration from ADIsimPLL and import the configuration into this application.
This application will then create the registers values for the ADIsimPLL configuration.
To export a configuration from ADIsimPLL, see image. This will automatically launch this application.
Alternatively, the txt file generated by ADIsimPLL can imported into this application by clicking Tools > Import ADIsimPLL txt file.
